{"questionId":"26258","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The height of a baseball after it is hit by a bat is modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>21</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is the height in metres above the ground and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time in seconds after the&nbsp;ball was hit.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the height of the ball above the ground at the instant it is hit by the bat.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;metres&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26258","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the height of the ball above the ground at the instant it is hit by the bat.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}